                  <persName id="t18320705-252-person2075">
                  WALTER 
                  PITMAN
               <interp inst="t18320705-252-person2075" type="surname" value="PITMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-252-person2075" type="given" value="WALTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-252-person2075" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18320705-252-viclabel1321" type="occupation">boot-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320705-252-victim2074 t18320705-252-viclabel1321"></join>. The prisoner was in my service for about a month - I missed some money, and on the 22nd of June I marked some silver and copper, put it into my till, and went out of the shop to get my breakfast, leaving the prisoner and the shopman there - I returned in about ten minutes, and found the till had been opened; I took the shopman and the prisoner, and accused them of it; they were desirous of being searched - when the officer came the prisoner took the money from his pocket, and said I have only 1s. 9d. about me, which my mother gave me last night; he was stripping to be searched- I said that is the money I lost, and the officer took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-252-person2076">
                  RICHARD 
                  SHEPPERD STEVENSON
               <interp inst="t18320705-252-person2076" type="surname" value="SHEPPERD STEVENSON"></interp>
